      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I would advise you to be cautious, as indigestion can sometimes be a symptom of a more serious issue. Taking a couple of extra antacids might not be a bad idea, but I'd recommend taking a Tums or another antacid specifically designed to neutralize stomach acid, and also consider taking a low-dose antacid or H2 blocker to help alleviate the discomfort. If the symptoms persist or worsen, you can always reassess and seek medical attention if necessary.",
